# grapher_implicit_ycircle_smoke.numos — Phase 10B. Plot the IMPLICIT equation
# y = x^2 + y^2. The RHS references y, so although the LHS is "y" this is NOT an
# explicit y=f(x): it is the circle x^2 + (y-0.5)^2 = 0.25 (radius 0.5, centre
# (0, 0.5)). Proves the classifier sends "y = <expr with y>" to the implicit
# renderer rather than the fast sampler. Warning-only (no golden).
log "implicit y-circle: start"
wait 200
open_app Grapher
wait 60
key down
key enter
# Type "y=x^2+y^2"
key y
key =
key x
key ^
key 2
key right
key +
key y
key ^
key 2
key enter
wait 80
key graph
wait 80
key zoom
key zoom
key zoom
wait 150
screenshot out/grapher_implicit_ycircle_smoke.ppm
assert_app Grapher
log "implicit y-circle: y=x^2+y^2 plotted"
